\( g'(x) = \left\{ 
\begin{array}{cc} 
\frac{1}{2}, & x = 0 \\
\frac{f(x)}{x} - \frac{1}{x^2} \int_{0}^{x} f(u) \, du, & x \neq 0 
\end{array} 
\right. \)



由于 \(\lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f(x)}{x} = 1\) 且 \( f(x) \) 连续，得到 \( f(0) = 0 \)。计算 \( g(x) = \int_{0}^{1} f(xt) \, dt = \left\{ 
\begin{array}{cc} 
0, & x = 0 \\
\frac{1}{x} \int_{0}^{x} f(u) \, du, & x \neq 0 
\end{array} 
\right. \)。所以，\( g'(0) = \lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{g(x) - g(0)}{x - 0} = \lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{\frac{1}{x} \int_{0}^{x} f(u) \, du}{x} = \lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{\int_{0}^{x} f(u) \, du}{x^2} \approx \lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{f(x)}{2x} = \frac{1}{2} \)。另外，由于 \(\lim_{x \rightarrow 0} g'(x) = \frac{1}{2} = g'(0)\)，因此 \( g'(x) \) 在 \( x = 0 \) 处连续。

